tests/e2e/nut-dummy
tests/e2e/ssh-target
# F-048: the image build copies source + installs the wheel — it never needs the
# test suite, docs, deploy manifests, or the mkdocs config. Excluding the whole
# `tests/` tree (not just the two e2e sub-dirs above) keeps a routine unit-test
# edit from busting the builder's wheel layer cache (the builder does `COPY .
# .`), which otherwise reinstalls every dependency on every test tweak.
tests
deploy
mkdocs.yml
# ISS-045: keep doc/tooling edits from busting the builder's wheel-layer cache
# (the builder does `COPY . .`). README.md is exempt — pyproject's
# long_description reads it during the wheel build.
docs
tools
coverage.xml
*.md
!README.md
